    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-05-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="55"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Senhor <persName type="from">Mendonça</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States of Brazil</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-05-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 31, 1894</hi>
                        </date>. (Received May 31.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of to-day, by which, referring to my interview yesterday with your
                    excellency in regard to the protection by your minister in Portugal of the
                    Brazilian citizens in that country during the suspension of the diplomatic
                    relations between Brazil and Portugal, your excellency informs me that the
                    minister of the United States at Lisbon will be instructed, by cable, to use his
                    friendly offices, with the acquiescence of the Portuguese Government, for the
                    protection of Brazilian citizens in Portugal or the Portuguese dependencies
                    during the present suspension of diplomatic relations between those two
                    countries, and that your excellency will further communicate to me such reply as
                    you may receive from Mr. Caruth.</p>
                <p>Thanking your excellency for this friendly assent of the American Government to
                    the desire of my Government,</p>
                <p>I avail, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Salvador de Mendonça.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
